<item>
            <title>[LU-12023] Tests should nto call modprobe directly</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12023</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some tests, namely conf-sanity 102, sanity-sec 31, lfsck-performance try to modprobe lustre modules directly which is not going to work when running out of build tree.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s load_module() function from test-framework.sh that should be used instead, though the semantic is somewhat different as it expects full path, but that&apos;s probably ok for our case since we know wher all the modules are and outside of the build tree it&apos;s smart enough to do modprobe&lt;/p&gt;</description>
